\f0\b\fs42 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs40 \cf0 Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.\
Brown bacon in nonstick skillet over medium high heat. Drain crisp bacon bits on paper towels.\
In a mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, Dijon, Swiss and scallions with cooked bacon. Transfer to a shallow small casserole or {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cookware-and-bakeware-materials/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 baking dish}} and bake until golden and bubbly at edges, 15 to 18 minutes. Top with chopped smoked almonds. Place dip on a platter and surround warm {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/casserole/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 casserole}} with breads and carrots for dipping.\
Variation: Swiss and Bacon Dip with {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/horseradish/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Horseradish}} - Stir in 2 rounded teaspoons prepared horseradish when combining cheese and bacon.\
